Deputy President William Ruto says he is ready to face whoever the opposition picks for the 2022 presidential race. Speaking a day after the one Kenya alliance announced plans to formalize the outfit, Ruto said he is not bothered by the ongoing building of coalitions crafted to defeat him. The DP who was speaking in Machakos today also took a swipe at ODM leader Odinga accusing him of derailing the Jubilee government's development agenda by pushing for constitutional reforms through the building bridges initiative. Our senior political affairs reporter Geff Kirui with the details